    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-04-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-04-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="196"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d196">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72111/2101</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">12 April, 1915</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Lansing</hi>: This seems to me admirable and
                    absolutely conclusive.</p>
                <p>I have altered one word; and a question arises in my mind as to another. Is it
                    possible to say what the note says about the clearance and yet not use the <hi
                        rend="underline">word</hi> fraud?</p>
                <p>Cordially and sincerely Yrs.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
